                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12616468" author="pi_song" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2008 12:41:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current implementation also doesn&apos;t seem to handle different order directions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;B = ORDER A BY $0 DESC, $1 ASC, $2 DESC, $3 ASC
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think implementation-wise, we should somehow implement PigWriteableComparator  using composite design pattern.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622656" author="alangates" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 19:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch provides raw comparators for pig types so that we can handle order by descending.  It uses hadoop&apos;s RawComparator interface, because these raw comparators can also implement Configurable.  The ascending/descending array is passed in the JobConf and then deserialized in the setConf call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Much of the work of this patch was actually done by Santhosh.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622737" author="olgan" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 23:21:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch committed. thanks, alan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
